Wash and dry all produce. Bring a large #pot of salted water to a boil. Preheat #oven to 200 degrees. Zest 1 tsp zest from @lemon{1}, then halve. Squeeze 2 TBSP juice into a small #bowl. Halve @shallot{½}. Peel and finely chop one half; save the other half for another use. Thinly slice @garlic{2%cloves}. Chop @parsley{¼%ounce}. Cut @Roma tomato{1} into small cubes.

Heat a drizzle of @olive oil{4%teaspoon} in a large, preferably nonstick pan over medium heat. Add @panko breadcrumbs{¼%cup} and a pinch of @salt{}. Toast, stirring often, until golden brown, about ~{5%minutes}. Remove from pan and set aside on a plate to cool.

Heat a large drizzle of olive oil in same pan over medium heat. Add @crab cakes{10%ounce} and cook until browned on bottom, about ~{4%minutes}. Flip and cook until browned on other side, about ~{4%minutes} more. Transfer crab cakes to a #baking sheet and place in #oven to keep warm.

Once water boils, add @tagliatelle{9%ounce} to #pot. Cook until just tender, about ~{2%minutes}. Scoop out and reserve ½ cup pasta cooking water, then drain. Immediately pour reserved cooking water into bowl with reserved 2 TBSP lemon juice, then add @flour{1%teaspoon}, 1 tsp lemon zest, and @chicken stock concentrate{1}. Whisk with a #fork until smooth. Stir in @capers{1%ounce} and their juice.

Melt 1 TBSP @butter{2%tablespoon} in pan used for crab cakes over medium-high heat. Stir in garlic, chopped shallot, and a pinch of @chili flakes{1%teaspoon}(if you like heat). Cook until fragrant, ~{30%seconds} to ~{1%minute}. Pour in pasta water mixture, bring to a boil, and cook until thickened, about ~{1%minute}. Remove pan from heat and stir in another 1 TBSP butter. Gently stir in tagliatelle and half the parsley. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Place panko, tomato, and remaining parsley in another small #bowl. Season with salt and pepper. Toss to combine. Divide pasta between plates or bowls and top with crab cakes. Scatter tomato mixture over top. Sprinkle with a drizzle of olive oil and chili flakes to taste.